</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E1DCAC8CFF8A7303FF32FF661845FD90" pageId="15" pageNumber="209" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="A979FF07FF8A7303FF32FF661845FD90" blockId="15.[136,608,176,616]" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis id="9BB22315FF8A7303FF32FF661B42FF31" bold="true" box="[136,265,177,201]" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">Etymology.</emphasis>
We dedicate this beautiful new species to the memory of the late Gloria Amparo Galeano Garcés (
<date id="DD78D9C7FF8A7303FE1CFF27186FFEF0" box="[422,548,240,264]" pageId="15" pageNumber="209" value="1958" valueMax="2016">1958–2016</date>
), one of the foremost Colombian botanists and agronomists and internationally renowned specialist in the taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName id="6EC68484FF8A7303FE4AFE861814FE91" box="[496,607,337,361]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="15" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Arecaceae</taxonomicName>
(palms), an important element in tropical forests including DTF (
<bibRefCitation id="CD5782F6FF8A7303FE7BFE471813FE50" author="Garcia GA" box="[449,600,400,424]" journalOrPublisher="Caldasia" pageId="15" pageNumber="209" pagination="1" part="38" refId="ref10309" refString="Garcia GA. 2016. A la memoria de la profesora Gloria Galeano. Caldasia 38 (1): iii-iii." title="A la memoria de la profesora Gloria Galeano" type="journal article" year="2016">García 2016</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CD5782F6FF8A7303FF32FE671BEDFE30" author="Olivares I &amp; Balslev H." box="[136,422,432,456]" journalOrPublisher="Bot. J. Linn. Soc." pageId="15" pageNumber="209" pagination="204 - 206" part="182" refId="ref11993" refString="Olivares I, Balslev H. 2016. Gloria Galeano (22.4.1958 - 23.3.2016). Bot. J. Linn. Soc. 182 (2): 204 - 206. doi: 10.1111 / boj. 12461." title="Gloria Galeano (22.4.1958 - 23.3.2016)" type="journal article" year="2016">Olivares and Balslev 2016</bibRefCitation>
). One of her last published papers was on the use of the bitter palm, 
<taxonomicName id="6EC68484FF8A7303FF62FE271B8FFDF0" box="[216,452,496,520]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Sabal" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="15" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mauritiiformis">
<emphasis id="9BB22315FF8A7303FF62FE271B8FFDF0" box="[216,452,496,520]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">Sabal mauritiiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for roofing in Piojó, 
<collectingRegion id="6B0231E5FF8A7303FEB8FDC71B2EFDD0" box="[258,357,528,552]" country="Colombia" name="Atlantico" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">Atlántico</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CD5782F6FF8A7303FE38FDC71B56FDB0" author="Andrade-Erazo V &amp; Galeano G." journalOrPublisher="Acta Biol. Colomb." pageId="15" pageNumber="209" pagination="141 - 150" part="21" refId="ref9027" refString="Andrade-Erazo V, Galeano G. 2016. La palma amarga (Sabal mauritiiformis, Arecaceae) en sistemas productivos del Caribe Colombiano: estudio de caso en Piojo, Atlantico. Acta Biol. Colomb. 21 (1): 141 - 150. doi: 10.15446 / abc. v 21 n 1.47280." title="La palma amarga (Sabal mauritiiformis, Arecaceae) en sistemas productivos del Caribe Colombiano: estudio de caso en Piojo, Atlantico" type="journal article" year="2016">Andrade-Erazo and Galeano 2016</bibRefCitation>
), the municipality of the 
<typeStatus id="767D41A5FF8A7303FD8BFDE61814FDB1" box="[561,607,561,585]" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="6EC68484FF8A7303FF46FD87184CFD90" box="[252,519,592,616]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Graphidaceae" genus="Phaeographis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="15" pageNumber="209" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="galeanoae">
<emphasis id="9BB22315FF8A7303FF46FD87184CFD90" box="[252,519,592,616]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">Phaeographis galeanoae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E1DCAC8CFF8A7303FF32FD461BFAF9D0" pageId="15" pageNumber="209" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A979FF07FF8A7303FF32FD461BFAF9D0" blockId="15.[136,608,656,1576]" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis id="9BB22315FF8A7303FF32FD461ABCFD51" bold="true" box="[136,247,657,681]" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="6EC68484FF8A7303FE1BFD47187CFD50" box="[417,567,656,680]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Graphidaceae" genus="Phaeographis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="15" pageNumber="209" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9BB22315FF8A7303FE1BFD47187CFD50" box="[417,567,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">Phaeographis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently not well-studied, but we were able to examine most of the 
<typeStatus id="767D41A5FF8A7303FE75FD061BB6FD11" box="[463,509,721,745]" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">type</typeStatus>
material of names belonging here. We found only three species with transversely septate ascospores, inspersed hymenium, dark brown to carbonized excipulum, and stictic acid chemistry. Among these, the eastern paleotropical 
<taxonomicName id="6EC68484FF8A7303FE90FC461A8AFC30" authority="(Kremp.) Vain." authorityName="Vain." baseAuthorityName="Kremp." class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Graphidaceae" genus="Phaeographis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="15" pageNumber="209" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="circumscripta">
<emphasis id="9BB22315FF8A7303FE90FC461BADFC50" box="[298,486,913,936]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">P. circumscripta</emphasis>
(Kremp.) Vain.
</taxonomicName>
[syn.: 
<taxonomicName id="6EC68484FF8A7303FEAFFC671855FC30" authority="Vain." authorityName="Vain." box="[277,542,944,968]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cimidae" genus="Graphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostropales" pageId="15" pageNumber="209" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pasaniae">
<emphasis id="9BB22315FF8A7303FEAFFC671B92FC30" box="[277,473,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">Graphis pasaniae</emphasis>
Vain.
</taxonomicName>
nom. inval.] differs in the distinct, apically strongly carbonized labia, fitting the concept of 
<taxonomicName id="6EC68484FF8A7303FF32FBC71BFCFBD0" authority="(Staiger 2002)" baseAuthorityName="Staiger" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[136,439,1040,1064]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Graphidaceae" genus="Platygramme" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="15" pageNumber="209" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9BB22315FF8A7303FF32FBC71B53FBD0" box="[136,280,1040,1064]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">Platygramme</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CD5782F6FF8A7303FE9FFBC71BFBFBD0" author="Staiger B." box="[293,432,1040,1064]" journalOrPublisher="Biblioth. Lichenol." pageId="15" pageNumber="209" pagination="1 - 526" part="85" refId="ref13164" refString="Staiger B. 2002. Die Flechtenfamilie Graphidaceae: Studien in Richtung einer naturlicheren Gliederung. Biblioth. Lichenol. 85: 1 - 526." title="Die Flechtenfamilie Graphidaceae: Studien in Richtung einer naturlicheren Gliederung" type="journal article" year="2002">Staiger 2002</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and the smaller (15–25 
<emphasis id="9BB22315FF8A7303FF5BFBE61ABBFBB0" box="[225,240,1073,1096]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">×</emphasis>
<quantity id="6E3E52E2FF8A7303FF47FBE71B12FBB0" box="[253,345,1072,1096]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="209" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 µm</quantity>
), consistently 5-septate ascospores. 
<taxonomicName id="6EC68484FF8A7303FEA2FB871AF0FB71" authority="Mull. Arg." authorityName="Mull. Arg." class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Graphidaceae" genus="Phaeographis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="15" pageNumber="209" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="9BB22315FF8A7303FEA2FB871844FB90" box="[280,527,1104,1128]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">Phaeographis bicolor</emphasis>
Müll. Arg.
</taxonomicName>
, also an eastern paleotropical species, forms much shorter and broader, irregularly branched lirellae, and the ascospores are larger (35–45 
<emphasis id="9BB22315FF8A7303FEE3FB061B23FB10" box="[345,360,1233,1256]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">×</emphasis>
<quantity id="6E3E52E2FF8A7303FECEFB071B95FB10" box="[372,478,1232,1256]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="15" pageNumber="209" unit="mm" value="10.0" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="9.0">9–11 µm</quantity>
). Finally, a third species also known from the eastern Paleotropics, 
<taxonomicName id="6EC68484FF8A7303FEA1FAC61845FAD1" authority="Mull. Arg." authorityName="Mull. Arg." box="[283,526,1296,1321]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Graphidaceae" genus="Phaeographis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="15" pageNumber="209" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="concava">
<emphasis id="9BB22315FF8A7303FEA1FAC61BDAFAD0" box="[283,401,1297,1320]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="209">P. concava</emphasis>
Müll. Arg.
</taxonomicName>
, differs in the consistently 5-septate ascospores and the shorter, irregularly branched lirellae with sunken disc and prominent margins covered by a thallus layer. The new species is quite conspicuous due to the dendroid lirellae and strong color contrast between the olivegreen thallus and the dark brown disc and white margin of the lirellae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
